SIMPLE: inexpediency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inexpediency
<hw>In`ex*pe"di*en*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
quality or state of being inexpedient; lack of fitness; unsuitableness
to the end or object; impropriety; <as>as, the <ex>inexpedience</ex> of
some measures</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is not the rigor but the <qex>inexpediency</qex> of laws and
acts of authority which makes them tyrannical.</q>
<rj><qau>Paley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inexpedient</ent>⟦br⟧
